         <abstract id="aspace_549db2a72438292de121a54ea087f3e4">The collection consists of printed material relating to the history, geography, and politics of the Ivory Coast. Also included are photographs and slides.</abstract>
         <langmaterial id="aspace_67f2340eba651dd3fbe256ec4c8221ac">
            <language>The materials are in English and French.</language>
         </langmaterial>
    
      </did>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_b2a3788c20d766b9453707ae5c6c3778">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Transferred from the African Collection Curator.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <userestrict id="aspace_71eace29aa893f6f75617f6be361a4ac">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright status for collection materials is unknown. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_c873bc8aaaf3bddd38c03bec20f8bf02">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Ivory Coast (Côte d'Ivoire) Collection (MS 1522). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <relatedmaterial id="aspace_56a58eb3ae12fde57ce33590761547c6">
         <head>Associated Materials</head>
         <p>African Collection, MS 605; African Postcard Collection, MS 1575; Pamphlet Collection, MS 1351. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </relatedmaterial>
      <arrangement id="aspace_b4497c6e5df57f95216daa9020dac2e2">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The material in the original accession is arranged chronologically, with photographs last. Additions to the collection may vary in arrangement.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_35ae806bcc1dfa060d39332b64b430a9">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of printed material relating to the history, geography, and politics of the Ivory Coast. Also included are photographs and slides.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_b0116431d24cdcac5a33734254a5c2f7">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
